<section class="conservation" id="conservation">
  <div class="container container-narrow">
    <h2 class="section-title text-center">Conservation and Regeneration</h2>
    <p class="lead text-center text-muted">
      The land holds more than structures.
    </p>

    <div class="conservation-intro">
      <p>
        Over 90% of the land is intended to remain in conservation. This is a
        stewardship commitment embedded in how the property is designed and operated,
        not a secondary consideration. The jungle is not the backdrop. It is the thing.
      </p>
      <p>
        Trails wind through the Atlantic Forest canopy, down the hillside, through to the
        ocean on the other side. In the mornings, howler monkeys move through the trees
        above the terrace. Toucans call from the understory. The air carries salt and
        green in equal measure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="conservation-content">
      <div class="conservation-block">
        <h3>Permaculture Projects</h3>
        <p>
          Active permaculture projects run on the land. The property is designed to
          produce food, demonstrate closed-loop systems, and teach regenerative land
          stewardship to guests, residents, and workshop participants. Agroforestry,
          composting, and food forests are part of the living infrastructure.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="conservation-block">
        <h3>Bio-Building Workshops</h3>
        <p>
          Bio-building workshops are part of the programming calendar. Participants
          learn to build with natural materials, expand structures by hand, and develop
          a practical literacy with the land. The workshops expand both the physical
          space and the people who attend them. Knowing how to build something real
          changes the way you see the world.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="conservation-block">
        <h3>Trails and Ocean Access</h3>
        <p>
          The property sits on a jungle hillside with trails leading to the ocean on
          the other side of the ridge. Hiking to waterfalls and mountain viewpoints
          is accessible directly from the property. The Atlantic Forest here rivals
          the Amazon in biodiversity. This is not a carefully manicured resort landscape.
          It is a real forest that happens to have a village in it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="conservation-block">
        <h3>Conservation Land Stewardship</h3>
        <p>
          The vision for Rosemary Dream includes long-term environmental stewardship
          as a core operating principle. This means prioritizing habitat, carbon
          sequestration, and ecosystem health alongside the hospitality and community
          programs. Investors are choosing to steward a living landscape, not just to
          hold a financial asset.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

